  "@type": "ActorManifest",
  "id": "did:web:etzhayyim.com:actor:kosatsu",
  "name": "kosatsu",
  "glyph": "高札",
  "displayName": "高札 — Crime/Sanctions Competing-Claim Board",
  "displayNameJa": "高札",
  "displayNameEn": "Kosatsu",
  "purpose": "Mirrors crime/sanctions DESIGNATIONS (OFAC/EU/UN/UK-OFSI/JP-MOF/Interpol/…) into the kotoba Datom log as append-only, ATTRIBUTED events; computes a politically-neutral DIVERGENCE view where jurisdictions disagree. etzhayyim authors no designation and asserts no verdict; a designation is asserter-relative by construction.",
  "description": "高札 (kosatsu) — the public notice-board, globalized and content-addressed. Every sanctions / export-control / wanted-notice DESIGNATION is an append-only EVENT posted by a NAMED asserting authority (OFAC / EU Council / UN SC / UK OFSI / JP-MOF / Interpol / counter-sanction bodies) against a subject, citing the authority's OWN program + primary publication. etzhayyim NEVER posts its own designation and NEVER asserts a subject is a criminal / guilty / a terrorist — those are UNREPRESENTABLE; kosatsu records, attributed, 'asserter A listed subject S under program P as-of T'. The distinctive object vs the sibling accountability actors is the COMPETING-CLAIM graph: the SAME subject under DIFFERENT asserters coexists as PARALLEL datoms; the graph never collapses them to one boolean 'is X sanctioned'. A computed DIVERGENCE view classifies each subject {contested | unanimous | single-asserter} and flags coverage-split (listed by some jurisdictions, never designated by others) — making the reality that 'what counts as a sanctionable act varies by political position' a first-class, neutral, computed FACT. A designation is an EVENT (status :listed | :delisted, append-only, as-of; a delisting is a new datom, never an overwrite; 非終末論). An accountability / due-process-visibility MAP, never a target-list and never an enforcement instruction (G9). Edge-primary (G2/G7): there is NO per-subject risk/guilt/threat score; divergence is computed on read from the designation edges. Sourced from PRIMARY publications only (G3): ≥2 of the authority's own citations; commercial screening terminals are a prohibited citation. no-server-key (G7) + outward-gated (G8): live list ingest + any publication are Council Lv6+ + operator + member-signature gated; R0 is design + offline analyzer + dry-run posts only.",
  "descriptionJa": "高札 (こうさつ) — 世界規模・content-addressed の公的掲示板。すべての制裁・輸出管理・指名手配の DESIGNATION(指定)を、名指しされた発令当局(OFAC/EU理事会/国連安保理/英OFSI/日本財務省/Interpol/対抗制裁機関)が subject に対して、当局自身の program と一次公表を引用して掲示した append-only の EVENT として kotoba Datom log に記録する。etzhayyim は自らの designation を一切掲示せず、subject を犯罪者・有罪・テロリストと断定しない(構造的に表現不能)。kosatsu は『発令者Aが subject S を program P の下で T時点に listed した』を attributed に記録するのみ。兄弟の説明責任 actor との違いは COMPETING-CLAIM グラフ — 同一 subject に対する異なる発令者の主張を PARALLEL な datom として並置し、『Xは制裁対象か』という単一の真偽値に決して畳み込まない。計算される DIVERGENCE ビューが各 subject を {contested(係争) | unanimous(一致) | single-asserter(単独)} に分類し、coverage-split(一部の法域は指定・他は未指定)を示す — 『何が制裁対象たる行為かは政治的立ち位置で変わる』という現実を、一級・中立・計算済みの FACT にする。designation は EVENT(status :listed|:delisted、append-only、as-of; delist は新 datom であり上書きしない; 非終末論)。説明責任・適正手続き可視化の地図であって target-list ではなく、執行命令でもない(G9)。edge-primary(G2/G7): subject ごとの risk/guilt/threat スコアは持たず、divergence は read 時に designation edge から計算。一次公表のみ(G3): 当局自身の出典 ≥2、商用スクリーニング端末は引用禁止。no-server-key(G7)+ outward-gated(G8): live ingest と公表は Council Lv6+ + operator + 本人署名 gated。R0 は設計 + offline analyzer + dry-run posts のみ。",
